name: Jampui Hills
short_description:
Region : Tripura
Elevation: 3050 Ft ASL – 3300 Ft ASL
Type : Single Origin Coffees
Strength : 2/4
Roast Profile : City Roast
Variety : Arabica

Content Main Body : This unique lemon-ey coffee hails from the Mizo Hills range in northern Tripura. These
Arabicas are cultivated alongside oranges at the highest point in the region by hardworking Mizo farmers. The fruit of their labour manifests into the cup with sweet, nutty and spicy tones. With neutral acidity, a medium body a citrusy aftertaste. A mild clean cup that transports you to the magnificent hills of North East of India.

Brewing Recommendation :Espresso | Milk Based

name: ARAKU VALLEY
short_description:
Region : Andhra Pradesh
Elevation: 2600- 2980 Ft ASL

Existence Precedes Essence ~ J.P.Sartre
